          and drinking. The tea leaves are placed in the cup and covered with 
          hot water. Green teas are usually infused with the lid off to prevent 
          over-brewing, while most other teas are steeped with the lid on. Hold 
          the lid in place to keep the leaves in the cup while decanting or sipping. 
          Great for tea drinking at work or while traveling.</font></p>
